Note:
Java to HIR Translator - Converts Java AST to High-level Intermediate Representation

This file translates Java Abstract Syntax Trees into HIR format,
preserving all Java-specific semantics for bidirectional translation.

Translation Features:
- Compilation units → HIR modules with package/import metadata
- Class/interface/enum/annotation declarations → HIR type definitions
- Generic type parameters and bounds → HIR generic metadata
- Modifiers and annotations → HIR attributes
- Methods, constructors, fields → HIR members
- Statements → HIR statement nodes
- Expressions → HIR expression nodes
- Lambda expressions → HIR lambda nodes
- Method references → HIR method reference nodes

HIR Preservation:
- All Java modifiers (public, private, protected, static, final, etc.)
- Generic type constraints (extends, super)
- Annotation values and attributes
- Type information for all expressions
- Java-specific semantics (checked exceptions, method references, etc.)

Dependencies:
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
- frontends/java/java_parser.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/java/java_parser.runa" as Parser

Note: ============================================================================
Note: HIR Structure Creation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Creates a HIR dictionary used to model structured nodes (modules, classes,
methods, statements) as keyed records. The header is two int64 slots:
entry count and entries pointer; buckets are lazily allocated on first
insert. Returns 0 on OOM.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_dict" returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR dictionary for structured data.
    Note: Header layout (must match the backend reader hir_to_java.runa):
    Note:   offset 0  entry_count   number of live (key,value) entries
    Note:   offset 8  entries       pointer to a packed array of 16-byte
    Note:                           (key@+0, value@+8) entries, 0 until first set
    Note:   offset 16 capacity      allocated entry slots in the entries array
    Note: The backend reads only offsets 0 and 8; offset 16 is private bookkeeping
    Note: that lets set_dict_value grow the entries array without rehashing.

    Let dict_size be 24
    Let dict be proc allocate from Layout with dict_size

    If dict is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with dict, 0, 0  Note: Entry count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with dict, 8, 0  Note: Entries array
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with dict, 16, 0  Note: Capacity

    Return dict
End Process

@Reasoning:
Creates an empty HIR list with a two-slot header (count, items pointer);
the items array is lazily allocated on first append, so empty-list
allocations remain cheap.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_list" returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR list for sequences.
    Note: Header layout (must match the backend reader hir_to_java.runa):
    Note:   offset 0  item_count   number of live items
    Note:   offset 8  items        pointer to a packed array of int64 item
    Note:                          pointers, 0 until first append
    Note:   offset 16 capacity     allocated item slots (private bookkeeping;
    Note:                          the backend reads only offsets 0 and 8)

    Let list_size be 24
    Let list be proc allocate from Layout with list_size

    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with list, 0, 0  Note: Item count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with list, 8, 0  Note: Items array
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with list, 16, 0  Note: Capacity

    Return list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Open-addressed linear-probing hash table insert/update. Lazily initializes
buckets on first call with capacity 16. Key collisions probe forward until
finding either the same key (update) or an empty slot (insert). If the
table is full, falls back to resize_hash_table and retries.
@End Reasoning
@Performance_Hints:
Amortized O(1) per insert under sufficient load factor; worst-case
O(capacity) on probing. Bucket entries are 24 bytes (key/value/next),
chosen to enable future chained-collision evolution without resizing the
slot.
@End Performance_Hints
Process called "set_dict_value" takes dict as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set a (key, value) entry, matching the backend reader's exact layout:
    Note: a packed array of 16-byte entries (string-pointer key at +0, value at
    Note: +8) with entry_count at dict offset 0 and the array pointer at offset 8.
    Note: Keys are StringCore string literals compared by CONTENT, so re-setting
    Note: an existing logical key updates in place rather than duplicating it -
    Note: distinct heap copies of the same key string must collapse to one entry.

    If dict is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let entry_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with dict, 0
    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with dict, 8
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with dict, 16

    Note: Update an existing entry whose key matches by content.
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than entry_count:
        Let entry_offset be index multiplied by 16
        Let existing_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entries, entry_offset
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with existing_key, key is equal to 1:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with entries, entry_offset plus 8, value
            Return 1
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Note: Grow the entries array when full (or allocate it on first insert).
    If entry_count is greater than or equal to capacity:
        Let new_capacity be capacity multiplied by 2
        If new_capacity is equal to 0:
            Set new_capacity to 8
        End If
        Let new_entries be proc allocate from Layout with new_capacity multiplied by 16
        If new_entries is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let copy_index be 0
        While copy_index is less than entry_count:
            Let src_offset be copy_index multiplied by 16
            Let copied_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entries, src_offset
            Let copied_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entries, src_offset plus 8
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with new_entries, src_offset, copied_key
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with new_entries, src_offset plus 8, copied_value
            Set copy_index to copy_index plus 1
        End While
        If entries is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with entries
        End If
        Set entries to new_entries
        Set capacity to new_capacity
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with dict, 8, entries
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with dict, 16, capacity
    End If

    Note: Append the new entry.
    Let append_offset be entry_count multiplied by 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with entries, append_offset, key
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with entries, append_offset plus 8, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with dict, 0, entry_count plus 1

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Appends item to a HIR list, lazily allocating an initial 16-slot items
array on first call. Each item is one int64 pointer; count is incremented
on success. Returns the list so callers can chain or rebind defensively
against backing-array reallocation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "add_to_list" takes list as Integer, item as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Append item to a HIR list, growing the backing array geometrically so
    Note: lists of arbitrary length (a class with many members, a method with
    Note: many statements) never overflow a fixed buffer. The items array starts
    Note: at 8 slots and doubles whenever full; count and pointer live in the
    Note: header at offsets 0 and 8, capacity at offset 16.

    If list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let item_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with list, 0
    Let items be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with list, 8
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with list, 16

    If item_count is greater than or equal to capacity:
        Let new_capacity be capacity multiplied by 2
        If new_capacity is equal to 0:
            Set new_capacity to 8
        End If
        Let new_items be proc allocate from Layout with new_capacity multiplied by 8
        If new_items is equal to 0:
            Return list
        End If
        Let copy_index be 0
        While copy_index is less than item_count:
            Let copied be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with items, copy_index multiplied by 8
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with new_items, copy_index multiplied by 8, copied
            Set copy_index to copy_index plus 1
        End While
        If items is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with items
        End If
        Set items to new_items
        Set capacity to new_capacity
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with list, 8, items
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with list, 16, capacity
    End If

    Let item_offset be item_count multiplied by 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with items, item_offset, item

    Set item_count to item_count plus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with list, 0, item_count

    Return list
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Main Translation Entry Point
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Public entry point for the Java->HIR translator. Validates a non-null AST,
verifies the root is a compilation unit, and dispatches to
translate_compilation_unit. Returns 0 for any other root form (which would
indicate a partial parse).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_to_hir" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate Java AST to HIR

    If ast is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 0

    If node_type is equal to AST_COMPILATION_UNIT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_compilation_unit with ast
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Compilation Unit Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Builds a HIR module dictionary keyed with node_type="module", package,
imports, and types. Children of the compilation unit are scanned three
times — once each for the optional package declaration (always first if
present), the run of import declarations, and the run of type declarations.
Producing fresh lists each pass keeps the resulting HIR module
self-contained.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_compilation_unit" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate compilation unit to HIR module

    Let hir_module be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_module, "node_type", "module"

    Note: Package declaration
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let first_child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let first_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with first_child, 0

        If first_type is equal to AST_PACKAGE_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Let package_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with first_child, 16
            proc set_dict_value with hir_module, "package", package_name
        End If
    End If

    Note: Import declarations
    Let imports be proc create_hir_list
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_IMPORT_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Let import_hir be proc translate_import_declaration with child
            Set imports to proc add_to_list with imports, import_hir
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    proc set_dict_value with hir_module, "imports", imports

    Note: Type declarations
    Let types be proc create_hir_list
    Set index to 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Set child to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Set child_type to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        Let is_type_decl be 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_CLASS_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Set is_type_decl to 1
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_INTERFACE_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Set is_type_decl to 1
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_ENUM_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Set is_type_decl to 1
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_ANNOTATION_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Set is_type_decl to 1
        End If

        If is_type_decl is equal to 1:
            Let type_hir be proc translate_type_declaration with child
            Set types to proc add_to_list with types, type_hir
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    proc set_dict_value with hir_module, "types", types

    Return hir_module
End Process

@Reasoning:
Produces a HIR import record with node_type="import", a name (possibly
wildcard form like java.util.*), and an optional is_static flag preserved
from the AST node's value slot.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_import_declaration" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate import declaration to HIR

    Let hir_import be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_import, "node_type", "import"

    Let import_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_import, "name", import_name

    Note: Check if static import
    Let is_static be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 24
    If is_static is not equal to 0:
        proc set_dict_value with hir_import, "is_static", 1
    End If

    Return hir_import
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type Declaration Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Dispatcher across class/interface/enum/annotation declaration node types,
delegating to the specialized translators. Returns 0 if the node tag does
not match any of the four — signals a malformed input.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_type_declaration" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate type declaration (class, interface, enum, annotation)

    Let node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 0

    If node_type is equal to AST_CLASS_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_class_declaration with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_INTERFACE_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_interface_declaration with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_ENUM_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_enum_declaration with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_ANNOTATION_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_annotation_declaration with ast
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds a HIR class_declaration dict by scanning the AST children in two
passes: first to pick up modifiers, type parameters, and extends (a
TYPE_REFERENCE child is treated as the super-type — the implements clause
arrives differently); second to collect member declarations (fields,
methods, constructors, nested types) into a "members" list. Two passes
preserve the canonical HIR field order without an explicit ordering map.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_class_declaration" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate class declaration to HIR

    Let hir_class be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_class, "node_type", "class_declaration"

    Let class_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_class, "name", class_name

    Note: Process children (modifiers, type parameters, extends, implements, members)
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let index be 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_MODIFIER_LIST from Parser:
            Let modifiers be proc translate_modifiers with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_class, "modifiers", modifiers
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_TYPE_PARAMETER from Parser:
            Let type_params be proc translate_type_parameters with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_class, "type_parameters", type_params
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_TYPE_REFERENCE from Parser:
            Let super_type be proc translate_type_reference with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_class, "extends", super_type
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Note: Members
    Let members be proc create_hir_list
    Set index to 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Set child to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Set child_type to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        Let is_member be 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_FIELD_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Set is_member to 1
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_METHOD_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Set is_member to 1
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_CONSTRUCTOR_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Set is_member to 1
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_CLASS_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Set is_member to 1
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_INTERFACE_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Set is_member to 1
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_ENUM_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Set is_member to 1
        End If

        If is_member is equal to 1:
            Let member_hir be proc translate_class_member with child
            Set members to proc add_to_list with members, member_hir
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    proc set_dict_value with hir_class, "members", members

    Return hir_class
End Process

@Reasoning:
Same shape as translate_class_declaration but for interfaces — no
extends-as-single-supertype channel (interfaces multi-extend, captured in
the parent translator's TypeList) and constructors are not legal members,
so the member pass only collects methods and fields.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_interface_declaration" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate interface declaration to HIR

    Let hir_interface be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_interface, "node_type", "interface_declaration"

    Let interface_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_interface, "name", interface_name

    Note: Process children
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let index be 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_MODIFIER_LIST from Parser:
            Let modifiers be proc translate_modifiers with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_interface, "modifiers", modifiers
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_TYPE_PARAMETER from Parser:
            Let type_params be proc translate_type_parameters with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_interface, "type_parameters", type_params
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Note: Members
    Let members be proc create_hir_list
    Set index to 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Set child to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Set child_type to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        Let is_member be 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_METHOD_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Set is_member to 1
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_FIELD_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Set is_member to 1
        End If

        If is_member is equal to 1:
            Let member_hir be proc translate_interface_member with child
            Set members to proc add_to_list with members, member_hir
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    proc set_dict_value with hir_interface, "members", members

    Return hir_interface
End Process

@Reasoning:
Produces a HIR enum_declaration carrying modifiers, the enum constant list,
and any body member declarations (methods, fields, constructors, nested types)
that follow the constants after a ';'. Constants are lowered via
translate_enum_constant; body members reuse translate_class_member so an enum
with behaviour round-trips with full fidelity, not just its constant set.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_enum_declaration" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate enum declaration to HIR

    Let hir_enum be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_enum, "node_type", "enum_declaration"

    Let enum_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_enum, "name", enum_name

    Note: Process children
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let index be 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_MODIFIER_LIST from Parser:
            Let modifiers be proc translate_modifiers with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_enum, "modifiers", modifiers
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Note: Enum constants
    Let constants be proc create_hir_list
    Set index to 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Set child to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Set child_type to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_ENUM_CONSTANT from Parser:
            Let constant_hir be proc translate_enum_constant with child
            Set constants to proc add_to_list with constants, constant_hir
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    proc set_dict_value with hir_enum, "constants", constants

    Note: Enum body member declarations (the methods/fields/constructors/nested
    Note: types that follow the constant list and its ';'). Each is lowered with
    Note: translate_class_member - the same path a class uses - into a "members"
    Note: list so the backend can re-emit the full enum body, not just constants.
    Let members be proc create_hir_list
    Set index to 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Set child to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Set child_type to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_METHOD_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Let method_member be proc translate_class_member with child
            If method_member is not equal to 0:
                proc add_to_list with members, method_member
            End If
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_FIELD_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Let field_member be proc translate_class_member with child
            If field_member is not equal to 0:
                proc add_to_list with members, field_member
            End If
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_CONSTRUCTOR_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Let ctor_member be proc translate_class_member with child
            If ctor_member is not equal to 0:
                proc add_to_list with members, ctor_member
            End If
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_CLASS_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Let class_member be proc translate_class_member with child
            If class_member is not equal to 0:
                proc add_to_list with members, class_member
            End If
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_INTERFACE_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Let iface_member be proc translate_class_member with child
            If iface_member is not equal to 0:
                proc add_to_list with members, iface_member
            End If
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_ENUM_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Let enum_member be proc translate_class_member with child
            If enum_member is not equal to 0:
                proc add_to_list with members, enum_member
            End If
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    proc set_dict_value with hir_enum, "members", members

    Return hir_enum
End Process

@Reasoning:
Enum constant translation captures the constant's name and its optional
constructor arguments. The parser attaches the argument list as an
AST_IDENTIFIER container child (the same wrapper used for call arguments);
its child expressions are lowered into an "arguments" HIR list so the backend
can re-emit `NAME(arg, ...)`. A per-constant class body, when present, is a
rare construct; its members are lowered via translate_class_member into a
"body" list so it survives the round trip.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_enum_constant" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate enum constant to HIR

    Let hir_constant be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_constant, "node_type", "enum_constant"

    Let constant_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_constant, "name", constant_name

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let index be 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_IDENTIFIER from Parser:
            Note: Constructor-argument list wrapper: lower each child expression.
            Let args be proc create_hir_list
            Let arg_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 32
            Let arg_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 40
            Let arg_index be 0
            While arg_index is less than arg_count:
                Let arg_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with arg_children, arg_index multiplied by 8
                Let arg_hir be proc translate_expression with arg_ast
                Set args to proc add_to_list with args, arg_hir
                Set arg_index to arg_index plus 1
            End While
            proc set_dict_value with hir_constant, "arguments", args
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_ANNOTATION from Parser:
            Note: Annotations on the constant are not part of round-trip scope.
            Set child_type to child_type
        Otherwise:
            Note: A per-constant class body: lower its members into a list.
            Let body_members be proc create_hir_list
            Let body_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 32
            Let body_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 40
            Let body_index be 0
            While body_index is less than body_count:
                Let member_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with body_children, body_index multiplied by 8
                Let member_hir be proc translate_class_member with member_ast
                If member_hir is not equal to 0:
                    Set body_members to proc add_to_list with body_members, member_hir
                End If
                Set body_index to body_index plus 1
            End While
            proc set_dict_value with hir_constant, "body", body_members
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_constant
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR for an annotation type declaration (@interface form). Records the name and
the element declarations - each annotation element is parsed as a parameterless
method declaration (Type name() [default value]) and is lowered through
translate_class_member into a "members" list so the backend re-emits the full
annotation body, including any default-value elements, rather than an empty {}.
The optional modifier list is carried under "modifiers".
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_annotation_declaration" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate annotation type declaration to HIR

    Let hir_annotation be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_annotation, "node_type", "annotation_declaration"

    Let annotation_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_annotation, "name", annotation_name

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let members be proc create_hir_list
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_MODIFIER_LIST from Parser:
            Let modifiers be proc translate_modifiers with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_annotation, "modifiers", modifiers
        Otherwise:
            Let member_hir be proc translate_class_member with child
            If member_hir is not equal to 0:
                proc add_to_list with members, member_hir
            End If
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    proc set_dict_value with hir_annotation, "members", members

    Return hir_annotation
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Modifiers and Annotations Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Flattens a MODIFIER_LIST AST into a HIR list. Annotation children are
recursively translated into HIR annotation dicts; identifier children
(plain keyword modifiers) contribute their token text as strings. The
resulting list is a heterogeneous sequence of strings and dicts — readers
discriminate by type.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_modifiers" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate modifiers and annotations to HIR

    Let modifiers_list be proc create_hir_list

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let index be 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_ANNOTATION from Parser:
            Let annotation_hir be proc translate_annotation with child
            Set modifiers_list to proc add_to_list with modifiers_list, annotation_hir
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_IDENTIFIER from Parser:
            Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 8
            Let modifier_text be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 8
            Set modifiers_list to proc add_to_list with modifiers_list, modifier_text
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return modifiers_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Translates a single annotation use site. Always emits node_type and name;
when arguments are present, translates each child as an expression and
attaches them as an "arguments" list. Absent arguments leave the key
unset so consumers can distinguish marker annotations from valued ones.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_annotation" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate annotation to HIR

    Let hir_annotation be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_annotation, "node_type", "annotation"

    Let annotation_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_annotation, "name", annotation_name

    Note: Annotation arguments
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let args be proc create_hir_list

        Let index be 0
        While index is less than child_count:
            Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
            Let arg_hir be proc translate_expression with child
            Set args to proc add_to_list with args, arg_hir
            Set index to index plus 1
        End While

        proc set_dict_value with hir_annotation, "arguments", args
    End If

    Return hir_annotation
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Member Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Class-member dispatcher: routes field/method/constructor/nested-type tags
to their dedicated translators. Returns 0 for unrecognized member tags so
the caller can skip silently rather than emit a malformed HIR member.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_class_member" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate class member to HIR

    Let node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 0

    If node_type is equal to AST_FIELD_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_field_declaration with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_METHOD_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_method_declaration with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_CONSTRUCTOR_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_constructor_declaration with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_CLASS_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_class_declaration with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_INTERFACE_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_interface_declaration with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_ENUM_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_enum_declaration with ast
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Interface-member dispatcher: only methods and fields are valid here.
Nested types under interfaces would be handled by the class-declaration
translator instead.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_interface_member" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate interface member to HIR

    Let node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 0

    If node_type is equal to AST_METHOD_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_method_declaration with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_FIELD_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_field_declaration with ast
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds a field_declaration HIR dict with name, modifiers, resolved type, and
an optional initializer. Modifier and type children funnel through their
dedicated translators; any other child is the initializer expression and is
lowered through translate_expression under the "initializer" key, which the
backend emits as ` = expr`.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_field_declaration" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate field declaration to HIR

    Let hir_field be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_field, "node_type", "field_declaration"

    Let field_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_field, "name", field_name

    Note: Process children
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let index be 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_MODIFIER_LIST from Parser:
            Let modifiers be proc translate_modifiers with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_field, "modifiers", modifiers
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_TYPE_REFERENCE from Parser:
            Let field_type be proc translate_type_reference with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_field, "type", field_type
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_ARRAY_TYPE from Parser:
            Set field_type to proc translate_type_reference with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_field, "type", field_type
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_GENERIC_TYPE from Parser:
            Let gen_type be proc translate_type_reference with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_field, "type", gen_type
        Otherwise:
            Note: Any remaining child is the field initializer expression.
            Let initializer be proc translate_expression with child
            If initializer is not equal to 0:
                proc set_dict_value with hir_field, "initializer", initializer
            End If
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_field
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds a method_declaration HIR dict in three passes: modifiers + return
type first (a TYPE_REFERENCE or ARRAY_TYPE child supplies the return), then
parameter list (matched via AST_IDENTIFIER wrapper around the parameter
sequence per the parser convention), then body (an AST_BLOCK child).
Abstract methods leave "body" unset; semantic analysis decides whether that
is permissible based on modifiers.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_method_declaration" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate method declaration to HIR

    Let hir_method be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_method, "node_type", "method_declaration"

    Let method_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_method, "name", method_name

    Note: Process children
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let index be 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_MODIFIER_LIST from Parser:
            Let modifiers be proc translate_modifiers with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_method, "modifiers", modifiers
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_TYPE_REFERENCE from Parser:
            Let return_type be proc translate_type_reference with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_method, "return_type", return_type
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_ARRAY_TYPE from Parser:
            Set return_type to proc translate_type_reference with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_method, "return_type", return_type
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Note: Parameters
    Set index to 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Set child to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Set child_type to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_IDENTIFIER from Parser:
            Note: This is the parameters list wrapper
            Let params be proc translate_parameter_list with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_method, "parameters", params
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Note: Method body
    Set index to 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Set child to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Set child_type to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_BLOCK from Parser:
            Let body be proc translate_block with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_method, "body", body
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Note: Annotation-element default value. An annotation element is parsed as a
    Note: parameterless method declaration with an optional 'default <expr>'; that
    Note: default is the lone expression child (not a modifier list, type, param
    Note: wrapper, or block). Capturing it here lets annotation bodies round-trip
    Note: with their defaults; regular methods never carry such a child so this is
    Note: a no-op for them.
    Set index to 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Set child to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Set child_type to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        Let is_structural be 0
        If child_type is equal to AST_MODIFIER_LIST from Parser:
            Set is_structural to 1
        End If
        If child_type is equal to AST_TYPE_REFERENCE from Parser:
            Set is_structural to 1
        End If
        If child_type is equal to AST_ARRAY_TYPE from Parser:
            Set is_structural to 1
        End If
        If child_type is equal to AST_IDENTIFIER from Parser:
            Set is_structural to 1
        End If
        If child_type is equal to AST_BLOCK from Parser:
            Set is_structural to 1
        End If

        If is_structural is equal to 0:
            Let default_value be proc translate_expression with child
            If default_value is not equal to 0:
                proc set_dict_value with hir_method, "default_value", default_value
            End If
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_method
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds a constructor_declaration HIR carrying the constructor name, its modifier
set, its parameter list, and its body block. A constructor mirrors a method
declaration minus the return type, so the children are scanned by node kind and
each is lowered through the same translators a method uses (translate_modifiers,
