        Let param_type be proc translate_type_reference with type_child
        proc set_dict_value with hir_param, "type", param_type
    End If

    Return hir_param
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type Reference Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Dispatcher across array, generic, wildcard, and simple reference type
shapes. Simple references handle two cases: a name field at offset 16
(qualified-name path) and a null name with a token providing the spelling
(primitive type path). The latter avoids creating a temporary string for
every primitive use.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_type_reference" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate type reference to HIR

    Let node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 0

    If node_type is equal to AST_ARRAY_TYPE from Parser:
        Return proc translate_array_type with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_GENERIC_TYPE from Parser:
        Return proc translate_generic_type with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_WILDCARD_TYPE from Parser:
        Return proc translate_wildcard_type with ast
    End If

    Note: Simple type reference
    Let hir_type be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_type, "node_type", "type_reference"

    Let type_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16

    If type_name is equal to 0:
        Note: Primitive type from token
        Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 8
        If token is not equal to 0:
            Set type_name to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 8
        End If
    End If

    proc set_dict_value with hir_type, "name", type_name

    Return hir_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits an array_type HIR dict with element_type set from the first child
(the underlying element type, itself recursively translated). Multi-
dimensional arrays naturally nest via repeated wrapping by the parser.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_array_type" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate array type to HIR

    Let hir_array be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_array, "node_type", "array_type"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let element_type_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let element_type be proc translate_type_reference with element_type_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_array, "element_type", element_type
    End If

    Return hir_array
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a generic_type HIR dict whose type_arguments list holds the
recursively-translated argument types. The base type name is provided by
the enclosing TYPE_REFERENCE — this node only carries the angle-bracket
payload.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_generic_type" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate generic type with type arguments to HIR

