Note: ============================================================================
Note: Statement Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Statement dispatcher. Routes block/if/while/for/return/throw/try/var-decl/
expr-stmt to their respective translators. Returns 0 for unrecognized
statement types (treated as no-op in the resulting HIR block list).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate statement to HIR

    Let node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 0

    If node_type is equal to AST_BLOCK from Parser:
        Return proc translate_block with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_IF_STATEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_if_statement with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_WHILE_STATEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_while_statement with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_DO_WHILE_STATEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_do_while_statement with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_FOR_STATEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_for_statement with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_ENHANCED_FOR from Parser:
        Return proc translate_enhanced_for with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_SWITCH_STATEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_switch_statement with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_BREAK_STATEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_break_statement with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_CONTINUE_STATEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_continue_statement with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_RETURN_STATEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_return_statement with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_THROW_STATEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_throw_statement with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_TRY_STATEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_try_statement with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_VARIABLE_DECLARATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_variable_declaration with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_EXPRESSION_STATEMENT from Parser:
        Return proc translate_expression_statement with ast
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Translates a block to a HIR block dict carrying a "statements" list.
Children that fail to translate (returning 0) are skipped rather than
included as nulls — keeps the HIR clean for downstream consumers.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_block" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate block statement to HIR

    Let hir_block be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_block, "node_type", "block"

    Let statements be proc create_hir_list

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let index be 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let stmt_hir be proc translate_statement with child
        If stmt_hir is not equal to 0:
            Set statements to proc add_to_list with statements, stmt_hir
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    proc set_dict_value with hir_block, "statements", statements

    Return hir_block
End Process

@Reasoning:
Positional child layout from the parser: [condition, then, optional else].
Translation reads each by fixed offset and attaches to condition/then/else
keys. else only appears when child_count is greater than 2.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_if_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate if statement to HIR

    Let hir_if be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_if, "node_type", "if_statement"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let condition_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let condition be proc translate_expression with condition_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_if, "condition", condition
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let then_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Let then_stmt be proc translate_statement with then_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_if, "then", then_stmt
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 2:
        Let else_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 16
        Let else_stmt be proc translate_statement with else_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_if, "else", else_stmt
    End If

    Return hir_if
End Process

@Reasoning:
Positional child layout: [condition, body]. Two reads at offsets 0 and 8
of the children pointer array yield the two pieces.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_while_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate while statement to HIR

    Let hir_while be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_while, "node_type", "while_statement"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let condition_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let condition be proc translate_expression with condition_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_while, "condition", condition
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let body_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Let body be proc translate_statement with body_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_while, "body", body
    End If

    Return hir_while
End Process

@Reasoning:
Positional child layout: [body, condition] - inverted relative to while because
a do-while evaluates the body first. Lowered to a "do_while_statement" dict
carrying "body" and "condition" so the backend can emit
'do <body> while (<condition>);'.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_do_while_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate do-while statement to HIR

    Let hir_do be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_do, "node_type", "do_while_statement"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let body_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let body be proc translate_statement with body_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_do, "body", body
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let condition_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Let condition be proc translate_expression with condition_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_do, "condition", condition
    End If

    Return hir_do
End Process

@Reasoning:
Positional child layout: [init, condition, update, body]. Each is optional
in the source for-loop syntax but always occupies its slot in the children
array if present. Each is translated with the appropriate translator
(statement for init, expression for condition/update, statement for body).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_for_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate for statement to HIR

    Let hir_for be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_for, "node_type", "for_statement"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Note: For statement children: init, condition, update, body

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let init_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let init be proc translate_statement with init_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_for, "init", init
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let condition_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Let condition be proc translate_expression with condition_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_for, "condition", condition
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 2:
        Let update_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 16
        Let update be proc translate_expression with update_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_for, "update", update
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 3:
        Let body_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 24
        Let body be proc translate_statement with body_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_for, "body", body
    End If

    Return hir_for
End Process

@Reasoning:
return [value]; — optional payload. When present, the first child is the
returned expression; emitted as "value" key. Empty returns leave the key
absent.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_return_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate return statement to HIR

    Let hir_return be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_return, "node_type", "return_statement"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let value_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let value be proc translate_expression with value_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_return, "value", value
    End If

    Return hir_return
End Process

@Reasoning:
throw exception; — single mandatory child becomes the "exception" key on
the HIR throw_statement dict.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_throw_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate throw statement to HIR

    Let hir_throw be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_throw, "node_type", "throw_statement"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let exception_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let exception be proc translate_expression with exception_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_throw, "exception", exception
    End If

    Return hir_throw
End Process

@Reasoning:
The parser lays the try statement's children out positionally as
[optional resources, try_block (AST_BLOCK), catch clauses (AST_CATCH_CLAUSE)*,
optional finally (AST_BLOCK)]. Because the parser uses a plain AST_BLOCK for
both the try body and the finally body, they are distinguished by position:
the FIRST AST_BLOCK is the try block; any SUBSEQUENT AST_BLOCK (which can only
appear after the catch clauses) is the finally block. Catch clauses accumulate
into a HIR list. Lists/blocks are attached only when present, keeping the HIR
minimal.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_try_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate try statement to HIR

    Let hir_try be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_try, "node_type", "try_statement"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let catch_clauses_list be proc create_hir_list
    Let finally_block be 0
    Let seen_try_block be 0

    Let index be 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_BLOCK from Parser:
            If seen_try_block is equal to 0:
                Let try_block be proc translate_block with child
                proc set_dict_value with hir_try, "try_block", try_block
                Set seen_try_block to 1
            Otherwise:
                Set finally_block to proc translate_block with child
            End If
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_CATCH_CLAUSE from Parser:
            Let catch_clause be proc translate_catch_clause with child
            proc add_to_list with catch_clauses_list, catch_clause
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Let catch_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with catch_clauses_list, 0
    If catch_count is greater than 0:
        proc set_dict_value with hir_try, "catch_clauses", catch_clauses_list
    End If

    If finally_block is not equal to 0:
        proc set_dict_value with hir_try, "finally_block", finally_block
    End If

    Return hir_try
End Process

@Reasoning:
Catch-clause translation surfaces all three semantic pieces: the exception
variable name (AST offset 16), the exception type (the AST_TYPE_REFERENCE
child), and the catch body (the AST_BLOCK child). The parser emits children as
[exception_type, catch_block], so the first type reference and first block are
read positionally and lowered recursively.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_catch_clause" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate catch clause to HIR

    Let hir_catch be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_catch, "node_type", "catch_clause"

    Let exception_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_catch, "exception_name", exception_name

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let index be 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_TYPE_REFERENCE from Parser:
            Let exception_type be proc translate_type_reference with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_catch, "exception_type", exception_type
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_BLOCK from Parser:
            Let catch_body be proc translate_block with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_catch, "body", catch_body
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_catch
End Process

@Reasoning:
Translates a local variable declaration. Positional child layout:
[type, optional initializer]. Type is always present; initializer is only
attached if child_count is greater than 1.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_variable_declaration" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate variable declaration to HIR

    Let hir_var be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_var, "node_type", "variable_declaration"

    Let var_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_var, "name", var_name

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let type_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let var_type be proc translate_type_reference with type_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_var, "type", var_type
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let init_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Let initializer be proc translate_expression with init_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_var, "initializer", initializer
    End If

    Return hir_var
End Process

@Reasoning:
Wraps a top-level expression as a statement node carrying it under
"expression". The wrapper preserves the statement/expression distinction
for downstream code that needs to know about side-effect contexts.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_expression_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate expression statement to HIR

    Let hir_expr_stmt be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_expr_stmt, "node_type", "expression_statement"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let expr_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let expression be proc translate_expression with expr_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_expr_stmt, "expression", expression
    End If

    Return hir_expr_stmt
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Expression Translation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Expression dispatcher. Routes binary/unary/call/member-access/array-access/
object-creation/lambda/method-reference/literal/identifier/ternary to their
specialized translators. Null AST returns 0; unknown tags return 0
(propagates as a translation gap).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_expression" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate expression to HIR

    If ast is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 0

    If node_type is equal to AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_binary_expression with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_UNARY_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_unary_expression with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_CALL_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_call_expression with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_MEMBER_ACCESS from Parser:
        Return proc translate_member_access with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_ARRAY_ACCESS from Parser:
        Return proc translate_array_access with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_OBJECT_CREATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_object_creation with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_ARRAY_CREATION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_array_creation with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_LAMBDA_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_lambda_expression with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_METHOD_REFERENCE from Parser:
        Return proc translate_method_reference with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_LITERAL from Parser:
        Return proc translate_literal with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_IDENTIFIER from Parser:
        Return proc translate_identifier with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_TERNARY_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_ternary_expression with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_CAST_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_cast_expression with ast
    End If

    If node_type is equal to AST_ASSIGNMENT_EXPRESSION from Parser:
        Return proc translate_assignment_expression with ast
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a binary_expression HIR dict with operator (token type integer from
the AST value slot), left, and right operand expressions. Operator is left
as a raw token-type integer — semantic mapping (e.g., '+' vs string-
concat) happens later.
@End Reasoning
@Reasoning:
Maps a parser operator TOKEN constant to the exact Java operator spelling as
a string. Storing the operator as a stable STRING in the HIR (rather than the
raw token integer) decouples the backend from the lexer's token numbering: the
backend emits the string verbatim with no token table of its own. Every binary,
unary, and assignment operator Java defines is covered; an unrecognized token
yields 0 so the caller can detect and report a lowering gap rather than emit a
silently wrong operator.
@End Reasoning
Process called "java_operator_string" takes token as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Arithmetic.
    If token is equal to 95:
        Return "+"
    End If
    If token is equal to 96:
        Return "-"
    End If
    If token is equal to 97:
        Return "*"
    End If
    If token is equal to 98:
        Return "/"
    End If
    If token is equal to 102:
        Return "%"
    End If
    Note: Equality / relational.
    If token is equal to 87:
        Return "=="
    End If
    If token is equal to 90:
        Return "!="
    End If
    If token is equal to 82:
        Return "<"
    End If
    If token is equal to 88:
        Return "<="
    End If
    If token is equal to 81:
        Return ">"
    End If
    If token is equal to 89:
        Return ">="
    End If
    Note: Logical.
    If token is equal to 91:
        Return "&&"
    End If
    If token is equal to 92:
        Return "||"
    End If
    Note: Bitwise / shift.
    If token is equal to 99:
        Return "&"
    End If
    If token is equal to 100:
        Return "|"
    End If
    If token is equal to 101:
        Return "^"
    End If
    If token is equal to 103:
        Return "<<"
    End If
    If token is equal to 104:
        Return ">>"
    End If
    If token is equal to 105:
        Return ">>>"
    End If
    Note: instanceof (parsed as a binary operator).
    If token is equal to 35:
        Return "instanceof"
    End If
    Note: Unary prefix / postfix.
    If token is equal to 83:
        Return "!"
    End If
    If token is equal to 84:
        Return "~"
    End If
    If token is equal to 93:
        Return "++"
    End If
    If token is equal to 94:
        Return "--"
    End If
    Note: Assignment family.
    If token is equal to 80:
        Return "="
    End If
    If token is equal to 110:
        Return "+="
    End If
    If token is equal to 111:
        Return "-="
    End If
    If token is equal to 112:
        Return "*="
    End If
    If token is equal to 113:
        Return "/="
    End If
    If token is equal to 117:
        Return "%="
    End If
    If token is equal to 114:
        Return "&="
    End If
    If token is equal to 115:
        Return "|="
    End If
    If token is equal to 116:
        Return "^="
    End If
    If token is equal to 118:
        Return "<<="
    End If
    If token is equal to 119:
        Return ">>="
    End If
    If token is equal to 120:
        Return ">>>="
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "translate_binary_expression" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate binary expression to HIR

    Let hir_binary be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_binary, "node_type", "binary_expression"

    Let operator_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 24
    Let operator be proc java_operator_string with operator_token
    proc set_dict_value with hir_binary, "operator", operator

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let left_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let left be proc translate_expression with left_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_binary, "left", left
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let right_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Let right be proc translate_expression with right_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_binary, "right", right
    End If

    Return hir_binary
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a unary_expression HIR dict with operator and single operand. Both
prefix and postfix unary forms share this node type — the operator value
distinguishes them when downstream code needs to differentiate ++x from
x++.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_unary_expression" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate unary expression to HIR

    Let hir_unary be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_unary, "node_type", "unary_expression"

    Let operator_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 24
    Let operator be proc java_operator_string with operator_token
    proc set_dict_value with hir_unary, "operator", operator

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let operand_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let operand be proc translate_expression with operand_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_unary, "operand", operand
    End If

    Return hir_unary
End Process

@Reasoning:
Positional child layout: [callee, args]. Callee is any expression
(typically an identifier or member access); args is a list-wrapper child
processed by translate_argument_list.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_call_expression" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate call expression to HIR

    Let hir_call be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_call, "node_type", "call_expression"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let callee_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let callee be proc translate_expression with callee_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_call, "callee", callee
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let args_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Let arguments be proc translate_argument_list with args_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_call, "arguments", arguments
    End If

    Return hir_call
End Process

@Reasoning:
Flattens a call's argument-list wrapper into a HIR list. Each child is
recursively translated as an expression and appended preserving source
order — argument order is positional in Java.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_argument_list" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate argument list to HIR

    Let args_list be proc create_hir_list

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let index be 0

    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let arg_hir be proc translate_expression with child
        Set args_list to proc add_to_list with args_list, arg_hir
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return args_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a member_access HIR dict with the member name (read from the AST
name slot) and an object expression. Chained accesses (a.b.c) come out as
nested member_access dicts because the parser builds them left-to-right.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_member_access" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate member access to HIR

    Let hir_member be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_member, "node_type", "member_access"

    Let member_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_member, "member", member_name

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let object_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let object_expr be proc translate_expression with object_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_member, "object", object_expr
    End If

    Return hir_member
End Process

@Reasoning:
Positional child layout: [array, index]. Both are expressions. Multi-
dimensional accesses come out as nested array_access dicts because the
parser builds a[i][j] left-to-right.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_array_access" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate array access to HIR

    Let hir_array_access be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_array_access, "node_type", "array_access"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let array_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let array_expr be proc translate_expression with array_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_array_access, "array", array_expr
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let index_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Let index_expr be proc translate_expression with index_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_array_access, "index", index_expr
    End If

    Return hir_array_access
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits an object_creation HIR dict with the type reference and an argument list.
When the source is an anonymous-class instantiation (new Runnable() { ... }) the
parser attaches the class body as a third AST_BLOCK child whose children are
class members; that body is lowered member-by-member into an "anonymous_body"
HIR list so the backend can re-emit the brace-enclosed member declarations.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_object_creation" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate object creation (new) to HIR

    Let hir_new be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_new, "node_type", "object_creation"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let type_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let type_ref be proc translate_type_reference with type_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_new, "type", type_ref
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let args_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Let arguments be proc translate_argument_list with args_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_new, "arguments", arguments
    End If

    Note: Optional anonymous-class body: the third child is an AST_BLOCK whose
    Note: children are member declarations. Lower each member into a HIR list.
    If child_count is greater than 2:
        Let body_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 16
        Let body_node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with body_ast, 0
        If body_node_type is equal to AST_BLOCK from Parser:
            Let members be proc create_hir_list
            Let body_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with body_ast, 32
            Let body_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with body_ast, 40
            Let mindex be 0
            While mindex is less than body_count:
                Let member_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with body_children, mindex multiplied by 8
                Let member_hir be proc translate_class_member with member_ast
                If member_hir is not equal to 0:
                    proc add_to_list with members, member_hir
                End If
                Set mindex to mindex plus 1
            End While
            proc set_dict_value with hir_new, "anonymous_body", members
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_new
End Process

@Reasoning:
Array creation has two shapes sharing AST_ARRAY_CREATION. A sized/typed array
('new T[n]', 'new T[]{...}') is flagged with value 0: its first child is the
element type, any following children that are size expressions populate a
"dimensions" list, and a trailing AST_ARRAY_CREATION child flagged value 1 is
the brace initializer. A bare initializer block ('{1, 2, 3}', as a field/local
RHS or nested element) is flagged value 1: it has no element-type child and all
its children are element expressions, lowered into an "elements" list. The
"is_initializer" key lets the backend pick '{...}' vs 'new T[...]' emission.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_array_creation" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate array creation / array initializer to HIR

    Let hir_array be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_array, "node_type", "array_creation"

    Let is_initializer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 24
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If is_initializer is equal to 1:
        Note: Pure initializer block: every child is an element expression.
        proc set_dict_value with hir_array, "is_initializer", 1
        Let elements be proc create_hir_list
        Let eindex be 0
        While eindex is less than child_count:
            Let element_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, eindex multiplied by 8
            Let element be proc translate_expression with element_ast
            If element is not equal to 0:
                proc add_to_list with elements, element
            End If
            Set eindex to eindex plus 1
        End While
        proc set_dict_value with hir_array, "elements", elements
        Return hir_array
    End If

    Note: Sized/typed array. children[0] is the element type; remaining children
    Note: are either dimension-size expressions or the trailing initializer block.
    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let type_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let element_type be proc translate_type_reference with type_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_array, "element_type", element_type
    End If

    Let dimensions be proc create_hir_list
    Let index be 1
    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0
        If child_node_type is equal to AST_ARRAY_CREATION from Parser:
            Note: The trailing brace initializer.
            Let initializer be proc translate_array_creation with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_array, "initializer", initializer
        Otherwise:
            Let dim_expr be proc translate_expression with child
            If dim_expr is not equal to 0:
                proc add_to_list with dimensions, dim_expr
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    proc set_dict_value with hir_array, "dimensions", dimensions

    Return hir_array
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a lambda_expression HIR dict. The parser places the parameters as the
first child (an AST_PARAMETER container whose own children are the individual
parameter nodes) and the body as the second child. Parameters are lowered with
translate_parameter_list into a HIR LIST of parameter dicts - the same shape a
method's parameter list uses, so the backend emits them through one code path.
The body is lowered as an expression (single-expression form) or block. The
functional-interface inference happens at the semantic level, not here, so the
HIR carries only the lambda's syntactic shape.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_lambda_expression" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate lambda expression to HIR

    Let hir_lambda be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_lambda, "node_type", "lambda_expression"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let params_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let parameters be proc translate_parameter_list with params_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_lambda, "parameters", parameters
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let body_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Note: A lambda body is either a block ({ ...statements... }) or a single
        Note: expression (x -> x + 1). Dispatch on the AST node kind so block-body
        Note: lambdas lower their statement sequence rather than being silently
        Note: dropped by the expression translator, which has no AST_BLOCK case.
        Let body_node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with body_ast, 0
        If body_node_type is equal to AST_BLOCK from Parser:
            Let block_body be proc translate_block with body_ast
            proc set_dict_value with hir_lambda, "body", block_body
            proc set_dict_value with hir_lambda, "body_is_block", 1
        Otherwise:
            Let expr_body be proc translate_expression with body_ast
            proc set_dict_value with hir_lambda, "body", expr_body
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_lambda
End Process

@Reasoning:
Java method references (`Class::method`, `instance::method`) are
shorthand for lambdas that just delegate to a method. HIR preserves
them as their own node kind ("method_reference") so downstream
consumers can choose to lower them as either function-pointer
references or inlined lambdas depending on target backend.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a HIR dict tagged "method_reference". Reads the method name
from AST offset 16 and attaches it. The target expression (the
left-hand side of `::`) is the first child of the AST node; reads
children pointer at offset 32 and child_count at offset 40; if at
least one child exists, recursively translates the first child as
the target and attaches it.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_method_reference" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate method reference (::) to HIR

    Let hir_method_ref be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_method_ref, "node_type", "method_reference"

    Let method_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_method_ref, "method", method_name

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let target_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let target be proc translate_expression with target_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_method_ref, "target", target
    End If

    Return hir_method_ref
End Process

@Reasoning:
Java ternary `cond ? then : else` becomes a three-child HIR node. The
three branches are translated recursively and stored under distinct
keys ("condition", "then", "else") rather than as positional children
so HIR consumers don't have to remember ordering.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a HIR dict tagged "ternary_expression". Reads children list
at offset 32 with child_count at offset 40. Each of the three sub-
expressions lives in a fixed slot: children[0] (condition),
children[1] (then), children[2] (else). Note the pointer arithmetic
uses raw byte offsets (0, 8, 16) into the children array because
each child is an 8-byte pointer. Each subexpression is recursively
translated via translate_expression before attaching.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_ternary_expression" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate ternary conditional expression to HIR

    Let hir_ternary be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_ternary, "node_type", "ternary_expression"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let condition_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let condition be proc translate_expression with condition_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_ternary, "condition", condition
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let then_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Let then_expr be proc translate_expression with then_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_ternary, "then", then_expr
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 2:
        Let else_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 16
        Let else_expr be proc translate_expression with else_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_ternary, "else", else_expr
    End If

    Return hir_ternary
End Process

@Reasoning:
Java literal translation preserves both the raw value string and the
token-type tag so downstream HIR consumers can distinguish int vs
long vs string literals without re-classifying. The literal value
itself lives at AST offset 24; the originating token (with its
type tag) at offset 8.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a HIR dict tagged "literal". Reads value from offset 24
and attaches as the "value" entry. Reads token pointer from offset
8; if non-null, reads token_type from token's offset 0 and attaches
as the "literal_type" entry. Missing token info results in no
literal_type entry — consumers must handle the absence.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_literal" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate literal value to HIR

    Let hir_literal be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_literal, "node_type", "literal"

    Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 24
    proc set_dict_value with hir_literal, "value", value

    Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 8
    If token is not equal to 0:
        Let token_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 0
        proc set_dict_value with hir_literal, "literal_type", token_type
    End If

    Return hir_literal
End Process

@Reasoning:
Identifier translation. The identifier carries only a name; its
resolved binding is the responsibility of a later semantic-analysis
pass that walks the HIR tree with a symbol-table context.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a HIR dict tagged "identifier" with the name string read from
AST offset 16. Attaches as the "name" entry.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_identifier" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate identifier to HIR

    Let hir_id be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_id, "node_type", "identifier"

    Let name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_id, "name", name

    Return hir_id
End Process

@Reasoning:
Enhanced for-each: for (Type name : collection) body. The loop variable's name
is on the node (offset 16); its declared type is the first AST_TYPE_REFERENCE
child; the collection expression and body statement follow. The HIR records
the variable name, element type, iterable expression, and body under named
keys so the backend reconstructs the `for (T n : expr) body` form exactly.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_enhanced_for" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate enhanced for-each statement to HIR

    Let hir_for be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_for, "node_type", "enhanced_for"

    Let var_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    proc set_dict_value with hir_for, "variable", var_name

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let index be 0
    Let seen_collection be 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_TYPE_REFERENCE from Parser:
            Let element_type be proc translate_type_reference with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_for, "element_type", element_type
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_ARRAY_TYPE from Parser:
            Let arr_type be proc translate_type_reference with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_for, "element_type", arr_type
        Otherwise If child_type is equal to AST_GENERIC_TYPE from Parser:
            Let gen_type be proc translate_type_reference with child
            proc set_dict_value with hir_for, "element_type", gen_type
        Otherwise:
            If seen_collection is equal to 0:
                Let collection be proc translate_expression with child
                proc set_dict_value with hir_for, "collection", collection
                Set seen_collection to 1
            Otherwise:
                Let body be proc translate_statement with child
                proc set_dict_value with hir_for, "body", body
            End If
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_for
End Process

@Reasoning:
A switch statement: the first child is the selector expression; the remaining
children are AST_CASE_STATEMENT nodes (both labeled cases and the default,
which is a case node flagged via its value slot). The selector is lowered as an
expression; the cases are lowered into a HIR list under "cases".
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_switch_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate switch statement to HIR

    Let hir_switch be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_switch, "node_type", "switch_statement"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let cases_list be proc create_hir_list

    Let index be 0
    Let seen_selector be 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_CASE_STATEMENT from Parser:
            Let case_hir be proc translate_case_statement with child
            proc add_to_list with cases_list, case_hir
        Otherwise:
            If seen_selector is equal to 0:
                Let selector be proc translate_expression with child
                proc set_dict_value with hir_switch, "selector", selector
                Set seen_selector to 1
            End If
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    proc set_dict_value with hir_switch, "cases", cases_list

    Return hir_switch
End Process

@Reasoning:
A case (or default) within a switch. The parser encodes the arm kind in the
node value slot: 0 = classic case, 1 = classic default, 2 = arrow case,
3 = arrow default. Classic arms carry their match value(s) as leading children
followed by a fall-through statement sequence terminated by the next arm. Arrow
arms carry their match value(s) (one or more, for 'case A, B ->') followed by
exactly one body node (a block or a single statement). The lowering records
is_default, is_arrow, the list of case values (under "values", with the first
also under "value" for single-label compatibility), and a HIR list of body
statements. For an arrow body that is a block the block's statements are
flattened into the same body list so the backend has a uniform statement
sequence to emit.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_case_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate switch case/default to HIR

    Let hir_case be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_case, "node_type", "case_statement"

    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 24
    Let is_default be 0
    If kind is equal to 1:
        Set is_default to 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 3:
        Set is_default to 1
    End If
    Let is_arrow be 0
    If kind is equal to 2:
        Set is_arrow to 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 3:
        Set is_arrow to 1
    End If

    If is_default is equal to 1:
        proc set_dict_value with hir_case, "is_default", 1
    End If
    If is_arrow is equal to 1:
        proc set_dict_value with hir_case, "is_arrow", 1
    End If

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Let values_list be proc create_hir_list
    Let body_list be proc create_hir_list

    Note: For arrow arms the LAST child is the body; all preceding children are
    Note: label value expressions. For classic arms the leading children up to the
    Note: first statement are the label value(s) and the rest are body statements;
    Note: a classic default has no value children. The arrow body's terminal
    Note: position lets us split values from body by index without inspecting
    Note: node kinds.
    Let body_start be child_count
    Let values_end be 0

    If is_arrow is equal to 1:
        Note: All children except the final one are label values (default has
        Note: none, so values_end stays 0 and body_start is the last index).
        If is_default is equal to 1:
            Set values_end to 0
        Otherwise:
            Set values_end to child_count minus 1
        End If
        Set body_start to child_count minus 1
    Otherwise:
        Note: Classic arm: the single leading value child (default has none),
        Note: then fall-through statements.
        If is_default is equal to 1:
            Set values_end to 0
        Otherwise:
            If child_count is greater than 0:
                Set values_end to 1
            Otherwise:
                Set values_end to 0
            End If
        End If
        Set body_start to values_end
    End If

    Let vindex be 0
    While vindex is less than values_end:
        Let value_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, vindex multiplied by 8
        Let case_value be proc translate_expression with value_ast
        proc add_to_list with values_list, case_value
        If vindex is equal to 0:
            proc set_dict_value with hir_case, "value", case_value
        End If
        Set vindex to vindex plus 1
    End While
    proc set_dict_value with hir_case, "values", values_list

    Let index be body_start
    While index is less than child_count:
        Let stmt_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let stmt_node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with stmt_ast, 0
        If stmt_node_type is equal to AST_BLOCK from Parser:
            Note: Flatten an arrow block body's statements into the case body list.
            Let block_children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with stmt_ast, 32
            Let block_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with stmt_ast, 40
            Let bindex be 0
            While bindex is less than block_count:
                Let block_stmt be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with block_children, bindex multiplied by 8
                Let block_stmt_hir be proc translate_statement with block_stmt
                If block_stmt_hir is not equal to 0:
                    proc add_to_list with body_list, block_stmt_hir
                End If
                Set bindex to bindex plus 1
            End While
        Otherwise:
            Let stmt_hir be proc translate_statement with stmt_ast
            If stmt_hir is not equal to 0:
                proc add_to_list with body_list, stmt_hir
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    proc set_dict_value with hir_case, "body", body_list

    Return hir_case
End Process

@Reasoning:
break [label]; - the optional label is the node's name. Emitted under "label"
when present so the backend reproduces a labeled break.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_break_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate break statement to HIR

    Let hir_break be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_break, "node_type", "break_statement"

    Let label be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    If label is not equal to 0:
        proc set_dict_value with hir_break, "label", label
    End If

    Return hir_break
End Process

@Reasoning:
continue [label]; - the optional label is the node's name. Emitted under
"label" when present so the backend reproduces a labeled continue.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_continue_statement" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate continue statement to HIR

    Let hir_continue be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_continue, "node_type", "continue_statement"

    Let label be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 16
    If label is not equal to 0:
        proc set_dict_value with hir_continue, "label", label
    End If

    Return hir_continue
End Process

@Reasoning:
A cast expression (Type) operand. The parser emits children [target_type,
value]. The HIR records the cast type and the operand under named keys so the
backend re-emits the parenthesized cast.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_cast_expression" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate cast expression to HIR

    Let hir_cast be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_cast, "node_type", "cast_expression"

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let type_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let cast_type be proc translate_type_reference with type_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_cast, "cast_type", cast_type
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let value_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Let value be proc translate_expression with value_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_cast, "value", value
    End If

    Return hir_cast
End Process

@Reasoning:
An assignment expression lhs OP rhs (OP is one of =, +=, ..., >>>=). The parser
stores the operator token in the value slot and emits children [lhs, rhs]. The
operator is normalized to its Java spelling via java_operator_string so the
backend emits it directly; both sides are lowered as expressions.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_assignment_expression" takes ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate assignment expression to HIR

    Let hir_assign be proc create_hir_dict

    proc set_dict_value with hir_assign, "node_type", "assignment_expression"

    Let operator_token be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 24
    Let operator be proc java_operator_string with operator_token
    proc set_dict_value with hir_assign, "operator", operator

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let target_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 0
        Let target be proc translate_expression with target_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_assign, "target", target
    End If

    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let value_ast be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, 8
        Let value be proc translate_expression with value_ast
        proc set_dict_value with hir_assign, "value", value
    End If

    Return hir_assign
End Process

Note: End of Java to HIR Translator
